radiographic_examinations.findings: Inflammatory stranding and small locules of extraluminal air in the right lower quadrant. The appendix is dilated with hyperenhancing walls and ill-defined tip. At least 2 distinct appendicoliths present. No focal consolidation or pleural effusion. Unremarkable visualized lung bases, heart, pericardium, liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, bilateral adrenal glands, kidneys, and intra-abdominal loops of small bowel. Trace free pelvic fluid noted, and a hemangioma within L2.
